The paper deals with the problem of estimating the maximum independent set of geometric objects in turnstile streams, which involves data structures and algorithms for processing large amounts of data. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of communication complexity and information theory, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with approximation algorithms and parameterized complexity, which are topics covered in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), respectively.
